name: Palazzo Braschi
description: Palazzo Braschi, a large palace in Rome, was once covered by a huge face of Mussolini and dozens of prints of the word "SI" (Italian for "yes"). It referred to the 1934 Italian general election, which was a simple yes-no vote for the Fascist Party list. This NFT is a modern take on this historical moment with Mussolini face replaced by a new fictitious despot named Gustav. By https://twitter.com/DonnetPA
